description: [Keydnap](https://attack.mitre.org/software/S0276) uses a resource fork to present a macOS JPEG or text file icon rather than the executable's icon assigned by the operating system.(Citation: OSX Keydnap malware)

external_references.description: Marc-Etienne M.Leveille. (2016, July 6). New OSX/Keydnap malware is hungry for credentials. Retrieved July 3, 2017.
